# React Native + Expo's Metro bundler does not understand pnpm's
# strict, symlinked layout — when a package re-exports from a
# transitive dep (e.g. `expo` → `expo-modules-core`) Metro fails to
# resolve the sub-dep. Switching to a hoisted layout puts every
# package directly under the workspace's `node_modules/`, which is
# what Metro expects.
#
# The Web UI (`vance-face`) is unaffected: Vite uses its own resolver
# and works equally well with either layout.
#
# Reference: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/monorepos/
node-linker=hoisted
